div.p:
- I like to have separate subnets for Public, Private, and Database workloads
- I have typically found the default ACLs to be sufficient when using Security Groups well
- The only change I would typically make to the default route table is to make sure that the private subnets route through the NAT gateway(s) for outbound traffic
- Here I've used the NAT gateway for the Lambda to communicate a response back to API Gateway, but could also use PrivateLink for a more direct path that may save a bit on cost.
